recruitment-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ELovable%20CEO%20Anton%20Osika%3C%2Fa%3E%20says%20he%20thinks%20people%20should%20stop%20seeing%20computer%20science%20degrees%20as%20a%20surefire%20way%20to%20land%20a%20career%20in%20tech.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20wouldn't%20say%20it's%20worthless%2C%20but%20I%20do%20think%20the%20leverage%20has%20moved%2C%26quot%3B%20Osika%20told%20Business%20Insider%20in%20an%20interview%20on%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOsika%2C%2035%2C%20said%20that%20while%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcomputer-science-major-myth-job-security-money-salary-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Egetting%20a%20computer%20science%20degree%3C%2Fa%3E%20%26quot%3Bisn't%20useless%2C%26quot%3B%20its%20value%20has%20shifted.%20%26quot%3BCuriosity%2C%20adaptability%2C%20and%20shipping%20high-quality%20products%20quickly%20can%20matter%20more%20than%20credentials%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20most%20people%2C%20a%20degree%20is%20no%20longer%20the%20entry%20ticket.%20You%20can%20build%2C%20ship%2C%20and%20even%20start%20companies%20without%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Osika%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20degree%20still%20has%20value%20if%20you%20want%20to%20go%20deep%20on%20systems%2C%20theory%2C%20or%20research.%20There's%20rigor%20there%20that%20tools%20won't%20replace.%20But%20the%20default%20path%20%E2%80%94%20'I%20need%20a%20CS%20degree%20to%20be%20relevant%20in%20tech'%20%E2%80%94%20feels%20much%20less%20true%20today%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20continued.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOsika%20said%20that%20in%20the%20past%2C%20the%20bottleneck%20to%20building%20in%20tech%20was%20the%20%26quot%3Btechnical%20know-how%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20required%20%26quot%3Byears%20of%20training%20to%20even%20get%20started.%26quot%3B%20But%20now%2C%20people%20have%20the%20tools%20to%20%26quot%3Bgo%20from%20idea%20to%20working%20product%20without%20ever%20touching%20a%20formal%20CS%20education%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOsika%20cofounded%20Lovable%20in%202023.%20Lovable%20is%20a%20vibe%20coding%20platform%20that%20allows%20people%20with%20limited%20programming%20knowledge%20to%20create%20software%20using%20AI.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOsika's%20startup%20has%2045%20employees%2C%20per%20PitchBook%2C%20and%20is%20hiring%20for%2016%20open%20positions%20on%20its%20careers%20page%20as%20of%20press%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20June%2C%20Business%20Insider%20reported%20that%20venture%20capital%20firm%20Accel%20was%20set%20to%20lead%20a%20new%20funding%20round%20in%20Lovable%20that%20would%20value%20it%20at%20%241.5%20billion.%20Accel%20was%20an%20early%20investor%20in%20Facebook%20and%20Slack.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpaul-graham-how-save-job-ai-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EPaul%20Graham%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20startup%20incubator%20Y%20Combinator%2C%20said%20in%20an%20X%20post%20on%20August%205%20that%20low-level%20programming%20jobs%20are%20%26quot%3Balready%20disappearing%26quot%3B%20thanks%20to%20AI.%20This%20is%20because%20AI%20is%20%26quot%3Bgood%20at%20scutwork%2C%26quot%3B%20Graham%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20at%20the%20same%20time%20the%20very%20best%20programmers%20(e.g.%20the%20ones%20who%20are%20good%20enough%20to%20start%20their%20own%20companies)%20are%20being%20paid%20exceptional%20amounts%2C%26quot%3B%20Graham%20wrote%20on%20X.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20I%20think%20the%20best%20general%20advice%20for%20protecting%20oneself%20from%20AI%20is%20to%20do%20something%20so%20well%20that%20you're%20operating%20way%20above%20the%20level%20of%20scutwork%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOsika%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20hiring%2C%20he%20is%20more%20interested%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flovable-ceo-looks-for-4-traits-when-hiring-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecandidate's%20ability%20to%20learn%3